    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>OIL REFINER PLANS OFFERING</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sinopec, China's largest oil refiner, plans to raise as much as $3.85 billion by selling 20 percent of its shares in New York and Hong Kong; Exxon Mobil Corp, BP Amoco PLC, Royal Dutch/Shell Group and ABB Ltd of Sweden have agreed to buy more than half of shares offered (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China's largest oil refiner, Sinopec, plans to raise as much as $3.85 billion by selling 20 percent of its shares in New York and Hong Kong next month. The company was carved out of the larger state-owned Sinopec Group to raise capital for the expansion of the country's energy industry. Exxon Mobil Corporation, BP Amoco P.L.C., Royal Dutch/Shell Group and ABB Ltd. of Sweden have already agreed to buy more than half of the shares offered.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
